SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 3507
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE INGLE.
7299H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 8, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to requirements for
on-site labor for state construction contracts.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 8, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 8.978, to read as follows:
8.978. All on-site construction labor for public works contracts and public
2 construction shall be employees of the entity working under the state contract. No
3 entity shall utilize independent contractors as laborers, mechanics, operators, or other
4 trades for a state contract.
✔
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

